latestPosts.caption:
Wearing a saree in Cannes should be accompanied with some drama right ?? And drama we got ! Rain , storm , hawayien and a 15 minute window before it started pouring again !!I 
All these years it never crossed my mind to ever put myself in a saree because where is the time ? And how will I work ??I
But sarees come very naturally to me , so once I draped it , I found myself strutting around and getting things done with utmost ease and comfort in this iconic and timeless @satyapaulindia piece . I think this will now be repeated more often when I travel ❤️

latestPosts.caption: Taking a moment before the Cannes mayhem begins to thank my personal assistant, travel agent, packer and accountant… oh and husband, who makes it all happen. #fyp #foryou #reels

Super chuffed to have been part of the 25 year gala celebration for Lakmé fashion week x FDCI.
Months of planning, prepping and gruelling hours but the teams did it !  Multiple brand and agency teams working nonstop to bring together icons of the industry all under one roof for a dazzling night. Thank you team FDCI , team Rise , team Lakmé for your faith and support . To do an entire week of fashion shows across many days and then end with a gala of this scale , it’s a tremendous feat . No wonder we danced like we had won a war😅
@lakmefashionwk @fdciofficial

Special thanks to @rahulmishra_7 @divyabmishra @justdeshiv for the dream dress and always having my back ❤️

latestPosts.caption: Found this photo lying in my drawer and floodgates opened. This is how I mostly remember us . Him always having my back . It’s been 8 long years today since my brother left us. But I always feel his presence , watching over us , having my back . We didn’t get the chance to grow old together but as each year passes I realise how much he continues to be a part of our life . I think back and see that so much of who I became in my foundation years had to do with him because he was this rock , always letting me to be as badass as I wanted to be . Siblings are so precious . I keep thinking about our crazy love hate relationships and realise how different we were and yet so so close . He was kind and humorous and bindaas and many good things to many people , but for me he was an exceptional brother at every step of life . Love like that only keeps us strong , even when they are gone …

latestPosts.caption: Time goes by so quickly ! Reminiscing holi over the years when kids would wake up early in the morning and go through multiple changes till they  had to be pulled back in the house . Tons of home made gujiyas and thandai followed by an afternoon nap to get ready for evening holi Milan  with neighbours . So glad we made these trips back to my hometown where we collected so many memories and stories . Missing Awadh ki holi little extra today !
